<br>
Sure it's silly to have to mash the thing over and over during a fight. But being able to mem it quickly rather than devote a spell slot to it, being able to throw it on the guy tank mezzing an add, being able to adapt to the situation rather than being locked into 'Only Player X gets +10% aggro for 10 minutes no matter what else happens', makes short duration spells more useful in combat than long ones.<br>
<br>
Of course, it would help if it actually had a noticeable effect.<br>
